<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-217-417 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 376 511  OV: 10 376 471.andM; </DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  Feb 25 1991 v8 n8 p85(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Howtek Inc. Personal Color Scanner. (Hardware Review) (one of fiveevaluations of color scanners) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Methvin, Dave.andM;</AUTHOR><SUMMARY>Howtek Inc's $1,995 Personal Color Scanner scanning deviceprovides extra-sharp scanning at 300 dots-per-inch (dpi), but itis twice as slow as other color scanning devices evaluated.andP;  Thedot-gradient test pattern taken at 300 dpi in extra-sharp mode hadespecially impressive results and there was almost no hint ofcolor mis-registration.andP;  The bundled software that comes with thePersonal Color Scanner is vastly different from the other bundledsoftware packages associated with the other scanning devicesevaluated.andP;  The Personal Color Scanner software, Scan-It, has aweak interface and uses video memory like a scratch pad.andM;</SUMMARY><DESCRIPT>Company:   Howtek Inc. (Products).andO;Ticker:    HTK.andO;Product:   Howtek Personal Color Scanner (Scanning device) (evaluation).andO;Topic:     EvaluationColorScanning Devices.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   Vital signs: Howtek Inc. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Howtek Inc.andM;PERSONAL COLOR SCANNERandM;The price to be paid for the stellar quality of the Howtek Personal ColorScanner is speed.andM;When the extra-sharp scan at 300 dpi was selected during PC Week Labs' tests,Howtek's scanner performed twice as slowly as the other reviewed colorscanners.andM;The quality of color scans of the dot-gradient test pattern at 300 dpi inextra-sharp mode was especially impressive during PC Week Labs' tests, withalmost no hint of color misregistration or aliasing.andM;Some photographs scanned in extra-sharp mode yielded some imperfectionsintroduced by the scanner, but this problem was usually filtered out byimage-processing software.andM;In normal scanning mode, the Howtek scanner delivered speeds comparable tothe other scanners, and the quality of the scanned image was also comparable.andM;Howtek's bundled software, Scan-It, is so vastly different from the softwareprovided with the four other color scanners that direct comparison isdifficult.andP;  PC Week Labs found the user interface weak during testing.andM;Scan-It uses video memory like a scratch pad, scanning at whatever resolutionis necessary to fill the screen.andP;  Once the user has selected the size of thearea of the document to be used, a new scan is performed at the final desiredresolution to save that area directly to disk.andP;  Other scanner softwarepackages scan at the desired resolution, then scale or scroll the image tofit onto the screen.andM;Howtek is working with Astral Development to complete drivers for PicturePublisher Plus.andP;  In addition, a version of Mathematica Inc.'s Tempra shouldalso be available soon.andP;  Howtek plans to bundle either of these packages withthe Personal Color Scanner for an additional $300.andM;------------------&quot;VITAL SIGNS&quot; DATAandM;Howtek Inc.andM;Hudson, N.H.andP;  (603) 882-5200andM;Publicly heldandM;Year established: 1984andM;Number of employees: 107andM;Gross annual revenue (1989): $18.4 millionandM;Gross annual loss (1989): $3.5andM;millionandM;Source.andP;  Information supplied by company.andM;</TEXT></DOC>